		<item>
		<title>Coil Joins the JS Foundation to Help Monetize Web Applications</title>
		<link>https://js.foundation/announcements/2018/10/10/coil-joins-the-js-foundation-to-help-monetize-web-applications</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Oct 2018 18:27:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kaitlyn Barnard]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Announcements]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://js.foundation/?p=2349</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>SAN FRANCISCO ‚Äì October 10, 2018 ‚Äì We‚Äôre excited to announce the newest member to join the JS Foundation, Coil, a community of content creators and contributors where contributors pay a monthly subscription and while they surf the web, Coil will pay out to the creators in real time. Coil...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://js.foundation/announcements/2018/10/10/coil-joins-the-js-foundation-to-help-monetize-web-applications">Coil Joins the JS Foundation to Help Monetize Web Applications</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://js.foundation">JS Foundation</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class=" wp-image-2350 alignright" src="https://js.foundation/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2018/10/coil-logo-300x158.png" alt="" width="260" height="137" srcset="https://js.foundation/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2018/10/coil-logo-300x158.png 300w, https://js.foundation/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2018/10/coil-logo-768x403.png 768w, https://js.foundation/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2018/10/coil-logo-1024x538.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 260px) 100vw, 260px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SAN FRANCISCO ‚Äì October 10, 2018 ‚Äì We‚Äôre excited to announce the newest member to join the JS Foundation, </span><a href="https://coil.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400">Coil</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a community of content creators and contributors where contributors pay a monthly subscription and while they surf the web, Coil will pay out to the creators in real time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Coil utilizes </span><a href="https://github.com/interledger/rfcs/blob/master/0028-web-monetization/0028-web-monetization.md"><span style="font-weight: 400">Web Monetization</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, an open source browser API that uses ILP (</span><a href="https://interledger.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400">Interledger</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> Protocol) micropayments to monetize a site. By enabling Web Monetization, website creators can securely receive donations while also providing rewards to any contributing users, creating a self-sustaining economy. The JavaScript reference implementation of the Interledger protocol, </span><a href="https://interledgerjs.org"><span style="font-weight: 400">Interledger.js</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, is one of the JS Foundation‚Äôs projects.</span></p>
